The daughter of the former EFF secretary general and attorney Godrich Gardee has been reported missing. The family offered a R100 000 reward for any information that will lead to her whereabouts.
Hillary Gardee (28) was last seen at about 17:40 on Friday April 29 at SPAR Plaza in Mbombela along with a three-year-old child.  ALSO READ: Babina Noko bolster coaching department with co-coach According to her brother, Moses Mbatha, the child belonged to another family member and she had just taken the child on an outing. Mbatha said the child was found on Friday evening at 20:30 in Umnenke Street in KaMagugu, but that Hillary is still missing.  A provincial police spokesperson, Col Donald Mdhluli, said Hillary resides in KaMagugu. Her family reported her missing to the Nelspruit police the next day, Saturday April 30.
Mdhluli said she was last seen wearing a black top and black trousers. She is approximately 1.6 metres tall and has a piercing on her nose.  The police asked that anyone with information that may assist in tracing Hillary Gardee, urgently contact Det Const Sthembile Zitha on 072 474 0835 or call the Crime Stop number on 08600 10111. Mbatha has also asked that they call the family on 072 514 1456. ALSO READ: The Lowveld Botanical Society revisits beautiful Tree Route